            "id": "5fd473ee996e47f58485a",
            "questionText": "A power plant delivers $!$4000\\text{ MWh}$!$ of electrical energy during a $!$5\\text{ hour}$!$ peak period. Calculate the average electrical power generated by the plant in megawatts ($!$\\text{MW}$!$).",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "897a170130b14f4d8b130",
                    "stepText": "Let's begin by identifying the formula that relates electrical energy to time in order to calculate power. Based on the concept of electrical power, which one of the following formulas should be used?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "b866d70e-adbe-4435-be21-c2c36ea664ca",
                        "64f6d809-190a-42c7-8bc9-a4f4eceaee29"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$P = \\frac{\\Delta E}{\\Delta t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
