            "questionText": "A solar farm is designed to create a voltage gain of $!$500\\,\\text{V}$!$ and $!$3600\\,\\text{C}$!$ of charge flows through the circuit per hour. Calculate the change in electrical potential energy, $!$\\Delta E$!$, in joules associated with this charge flow during one hour using the formula $!$V = \\frac{\\Delta E}{Q}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "aa5cf913676643869a27a",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct formula that relates voltage, change in electrical potential energy, and charge. Please choose the correct formula from the options below.",
